Vice President Biden condemns the targeted attack on law enforcement in Baton Rouge, where three police officers were killed and three others were wounded. He describes the attack as despicable, cowardly, and an attack on our way of life and rule of law. Biden emphasizes that police officers are a remarkable group of men and women who willingly put themselves in danger to protect their communities. He expresses gratitude towards them and urges people to not let others divide us. Biden sends his condolences to the families of the fallen officers and thanks all the police officers who are currently protecting us. He concludes by saying, "May God bless the fallen, their families, and their brothers and sisters in uniform."